data.enText: the act or policy of censoring books, etc.
The decree imposed strict censorship of the media.
data.chText: 这个法令强制实行严格的媒体审查制度。

tr: deleting parts of publications or correspondence or theatrical performances
counterintelligence achieved by banning or deleting any information of value to the enemy

example.ex: The government today announced that press censorship was being lifted.
example.tran: 政府今天宣布将取消新闻审查制度。

value.def: Censorship is the censoring of books, plays, films, or reports, especially by government officials, because they are considered immoral or secret in some way.
value.tran: (尤指政府官员对书刊、戏剧、电影、报道等的)审查，检查
